06/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania plans to host a meeting of the presidents of Western Balkan states in the near future, ATA reported Saturday (4 December).
The participants will discuss inter-religious and interethnic dialogue and tolerance, as well as the region's joint efforts towards EU integration.
In other news, the Albanian government decided on Friday to proclaim a 22-year-old US Marine corporal killed in Fallujah an Albanian martyr.
Gentian Marku emigrated to the United States when he was 14.
(ATA - 04/12/04;
AP - 03/12/04)
